Data Catalog for dw_Gold Layer
Overview

The dw_Gold layer represents the business-ready analytical layer of the data warehouse. It is designed using a star schema and contains:

Dimension tables → descriptive attributes

Fact tables → transactional metrics

This layer is optimized for reporting, dashboards, and KPI analysis.

## dw_Gold.dim_customer

**Purpose:** Stores enriched customer data including demographic and geographic attributes.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
| Column Name      | Data Type   | Description                                             |
|------------------|-------------|---------------------------------------------------------|
| Customer_Key     | BIGINT      | Surrogate key uniquely identifying each customer record |
| Customer_Id      | INT         | Unique identifier assigned to the customer              |
| Customer_Number  | VARCHAR(50) | Alphanumeric identifier used for tracking customers     |
| First_Name       | VARCHAR(50) | Customer's first name                                   |
| Last_Name        | VARCHAR(50) | Customer's last name                                    |
| Country          | VARCHAR(50) | Country of residence                                    |
| Marital_Status   | VARCHAR(50) | Marital status (e.g., Married, Single)                  |
| Birthday         | DATE        | Customer's date of birth                                |
| Gender           | VARCHAR(50) | Gender of the customer                                  |
| Created_Date     | DATE        | Record creation date                                    |
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

## dw_Gold.dim_product

**Purpose:** Contains product-level details and classifications.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
| Column Name     | Data Type   | Description                                     |
|-----------------|-------------|-------------------------------------------------|
| Product_Key     | BIGINT      | Surrogate key uniquely identifying each product |
| Product_Id      | INT         | Internal product identifier                     |
| Product_number  | VARCHAR(50) | Alphanumeric product code                       |
| Product_Name    | VARCHAR(50) | Name of the product                             |
| Category_Id     | VARCHAR(50) | Identifier for product category                 |
| Category        | VARCHAR(50) | High-level product category                     |
| Subcategory     | VARCHAR(50) | Detailed product classification                 |
| Maintenance     | VARCHAR(50) | Indicates if maintenance is required (Yes/No)   |
| Cost            | INT         | Base cost of the product                        |
| Product_Line    | VARCHAR(50) | Product line (e.g., Road, Mountain)             |
| Start_Date      | DATE        | Product availability start date                 |
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------


## dw_Gold.fact_sales

**Purpose:** Stores transactional sales data for analytics.
---------------------------------------------------------------------
| Column Name    | Data Type  | Description                         |
|----------------|------------|-------------------------------------|
| Order_Number   | VARCHAR(50)| Unique identifier for each order    |
| Product_Key    | BIGINT     | Foreign key linking to dim_product  |
| Customer_Key   | BIGINT     | Foreign key linking to dim_customer |
| Order_Date     | DATE       | Date when the order was placed      |
| Shipping_Date  | DATE       | Date when the order was shipped     |
| Due_Date       | DATE       | Payment due date                    |
| Sales_Amount   | INT        | Total sales value                   |
| Quantity       | INT        | Number of units ordered             |
| Price          | INT        | Price per unit                      |
---------------------------------------------------------------------
